Feature Details
F1 — AI Prophet Creation
- Seeded exactly three fixed ideologies: The Oracle, The Virus, and The Collective.
- Added `generateIdeology(spec)` with MOCK_LLM support and strict JSON parsing.
- Added `mintProphetIdentity()` for ERC-8004 minting, with mock token IDs in demo mode.
- Added prophet card endpoint returning `{ name, doctrine, personality, specialAbility, endpoint }`.
- Persisted ideologies, prophets, doctrine versions, and seed events through the repository layer.

Special Ability Engine
- Added `checkAndFulfillPredictions()` for Oracle keyword-based prediction fulfillment.
- Added `recordInfectionTick()` and `getInfectionTier()` for Virus infection state.
- Added `tallyVotes(seed?)` for deterministic Collective vote simulations.
- Added unit tests for all three mechanics.

F5 — Reflection Cycle
- Added concurrent reflection over all ideologies using `Promise.all`.
- Added strict JSON validation for reflection output.
- Added doctrine version writes, doctrine updates, and `doctrine_change` event writes.
- Added manual `POST /api/reflect` route and scheduler helper.

F7 — Schism Generator
- Added criticism threshold-based schism generation with tunable env threshold.
- Added descendant-themed prompting so new ideologies stay tied to the parent ability/theme.
- Added follower splitting, new prophet creation, identity minting, schism rows, and schism events.
- Added manual `POST /api/schism` route.

Validation
- `pnpm typecheck` ✅
- `pnpm test` ✅

Notes
- `MOCK_LLM=true` is the default, so teammates can build against deterministic output immediately.
- `DATABASE_URL` enables the Neon-backed repository; otherwise the in-memory repository is used for local/testing flows.
